ut also of darknesses, fears, and unspokens that Faulkner unveiled in the American psyche.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNovelists, AmericanxFamily relationshipsx20th century. 0aNovelists, Americany20th centuryxFamily relationships. 0aWomen in literature. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014243340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300142433423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300142433/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles